ntions:\n-   **Inputs**: Stored in a directory (defaulting to `fixtures/inputs`) with a `params.json` file.\n-   **Outputs**: Stored in a directory (defaulting to `fixtures/outputs`) with a `result.json` file.\n-   **Format**: JSON is used for both parameters and results.\n\n### 3. Companion Channel Responses\nThe `workflow.json` indicates that the agent's output is expected to follow a schema:\n```json\n\"output_schema\": {\n  \"reply\": \"string\"\n}\n```\nThe final workflow outputs mapping shows how these are exposed:\n```json\n\"outputs\": {\n  \"last_reply\": \"steps.reply_with_agent.output.reply\",\n  \"status\": \"steps.send_reply.output.status\"\n}\n```\n\nI have also launched a background agent (`bg_cc3bcfa3`) to perform a deeper dive into the `context/`, `runtime/`, and `steps/` directories to provide more concrete examples and confirm these conventions across all steps. I will report back once those results are ready.\n\n<task_metadata>\nsession_id: ses_2457184d2ffetQ1Uw27TZB3KjX\n</task_metadata>\n\nto continue: task(session_id=\"ses_2457184d2ffetQ1Uw27TZB3KjX\", load_skills=[], run_in_background=false, prompt=\"...\")","metadata":{"truncated":false,"prompt":"Explore this workflow directory to identify input/output file conventions and how companion channel responses are structured. Be concise and focus on files, formats, and examples. Thoroughness: medium.","agent":"Sisyphus-Junior","category":"quick","load_skills":[],"description":"Inspect workflow patterns","run_in_background":false,"sessionId":"ses_2457184d2ffetQ1Uw27TZB3KjX","command":"analyze-mode","model":{"providerID":"MoreCode","modelID":"gemini-3-flash"}},"title":"Inspect workflow patterns","time":{"start":1776951393027,"end":1776951439797}},"id":"prt_dba8e7afb001t2PWKSkJM8DiK6","sessionID":"ses_24571ebebffeQ0DrI18pbglq7M","messageID":"msg_dba8e14d7001FAD4ftGxhEbaRR"}}
